      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold first {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Bind with the yolk of the first {{eggs}} and {{water}}. Chill an hour. Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll, line a 23 cm tart tin, trim, prick. Blind-bake with beans for 15 minutes, remove beans and bake another 5 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Frangipane, plums on top",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the softened second {{unsalted-butter}} with the second {{caster-sugar}} until pale and creamed. Beat in the two {{eggs}}. Fold in the {{almond-flour}}, second {{plain-flour}} and {{almond-extract}} for the frangipane. Spread evenly into the warm pastry case. Press the quartered {{plums}} cut-side up across the surface, packing them in. Scatter the {{almonds-flaked}} and {{demerara-sugar}} over.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 35 to 40 minutes; the frangipane should be set and deep gold around the plums, the plums should look slightly burnished, and a skewer through the frangipane should come out clean. Cool fully in the tin before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
